  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies CICP (ITU-T H.273) transfer characteristics for creating a color space.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKColorspaceTransferFnCicp` enumerates the CICP (Coding Independent Code Points, ITU-T H.273)
transfer characteristic values supported by Skia. The transfer function describes the opto-electronic
conversion (the gamma curve) used to encode pixel values.

Use this enumeration with <xref:SkiaSharp.SKColorSpace.CreateCicp*> to create a color space
from a CICP primaries and transfer function pair.

## Examples

```csharp
var colorSpace = SKColorSpace.CreateCicp(
    SKColorspacePrimariesCicp.Rec2020,
    SKColorspaceTransferFnCicp.Hlg);
```
]]></format></remarks>
